---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const bookTitle = 'Modern Compass';
const newsletterUrl = 'https://newsletter.themoderncompass.io';
---

<Layout>
  <section class="book">
    <h1>{bookTitle}</h1>
    <p class="subtitle">Practical frameworks to help you navigate life with clarity and conviction.</p>

    <div class="content">
<!-- Left column -->
<div class="details">
  <img
    src="/book-graphic.png"
    alt="Modern Compass book cover"
    class="book-graphic"
    width="780"
    height="780"
    loading="eager"
    decoding="async"
    sizes="(min-width: 768px) 320px, 70vw"
  />

  <h2>About the Book</h2>
  <p>
    Modern Compass is for people who are tired of vague or academic advice and want something practical they can use to see real growth in their own lives.
    There are strong personal growth books out there, but many fall into the trap of focusing too heavily on research without offering tools you can apply. Others lean on outdated approaches that do not fit digital lifestyles, or they inspire without giving you a way to move forward.
  </p>
  <p>
    Modern Compass takes a different approach. Every chapter includes practical and approachable activities you can put into action. The Modern Compass printout is also a living tool that helps you track your growth over time across the four life directions and the layers within each.
  </p>

  <h2>Who It Is For</h2>
  <ul class="bullets">
    <li>You feel stuck in loops of intention without action.</li>
    <li>You want clarity in relationships, career, or personal growth and do not know where to start.</li>
    <li>You have read personal growth books and ended up back in the same patterns.</li>
    <li>You want more than motivation. You want a compass you can carry with you.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>What You Will Gain</h2>
  <ul class="bullets">
    <li>Confidence that grows from real world action instead of waiting for validation.</li>
    <li>Character that shows up as aligned choices you can point to.</li>
    <li>Trust that is informed and calibrated so you know when to extend it and when to hold back.</li>
    <li>Relationships that deepen past surface connection or confidence to release those that are no longer healthy to maintain.</li>
    <li>Momentum that replaces cycles of hope and inaction that starts with you.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Why It Matters</h2>
  <p>
    Most people drift. They wait for a breakthrough or a sign. Nothing shifts until you take ownership of your direction. Modern Compass helps you build a personal system that keeps you moving forward even when life gets messy or foggy. It helps you stop second guessing and start navigating with conviction.
  </p>
</div>

      <!-- Right column -->
      <aside class="sidebar">
        <section class="excerpt">
          <h2>Excerpts</h2>

          <blockquote class="quote">
            Profound trust is the rare moment when you know without needing to ask that someone would
            protect the most vulnerable parts of you even if it cost them something.
          </blockquote>

          <blockquote class="quote">
            Confidence does not come from ignoring what people think. It grows when you apply yourself in
            the real world and build evidence of your own ability.
          </blockquote>

          <blockquote class="quote">
            Hope does not change outcomes. Action does. Without it we loop in the same patterns expecting
            different results from the same choices.
          </blockquote>
        </section>

       <section class="card orange">
          <h3>Publishing Approach</h3>
          <p>
            I plan to self publish so the book can stay practical and unfiltered. The goal is a clear
            and useful read with frameworks you can put to work the same day you open it.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="card blue">
          <h3>Be Part of the Journey and Get Early Access</h3>
          <p>
Modern Compass is still in progress, and you can be part of shaping it. By joining the newsletter youâ€™ll get:
Fresh excerpts and behind-the-scenes thinking
Practical tools you can try right away
The chance to raise your hand for early access to the introduction and one life direction (Self, Relationships, or Trust) before the full book is finished.
          </p>
          <a class="text-link" href={newsletterUrl} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Sign up for early access</a>
        </section>

       <section class="card purple">
          <h3>How to Engage</h3>
          <ul class="checklist">
            <li>Subscribe to the newsletter.</li>
            <li>Reply to share your take on excerpts and tools.</li>
            <li>Try the worksheets and tell me what improved or what felt unclear.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>
      </aside>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .book {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1.5rem;
  }

  .book h1 {
    font-size: 2rem;
    color: var(--primary-color);
    margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
  }

  .subtitle {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    color: var(--secondary-color);
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .content {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 2rem;
  }

  @media (min-width: 768px) {
    .content {
      flex-direction: row;
      align-items: flex-start;
    }
  }

  .details,
  .sidebar {
    flex: 1;
  }

  .details h2,
  .excerpt h2 {
    font-size: 1.375rem;
    color: var(--primary-color);
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .details p {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .bullets {
    margin: 0 0 1rem 1rem;
    padding: 0;
    list-style: disc;
  }
  .bullets li { margin: 0.25rem 0; }

  .cta-box {
    margin-top: 1rem;
    padding: 1rem;
    border-left: 4px solid var(--primary-color);
    background-color: #f6f7f8;
    border-radius: 6px;
  }
  .cta-box h3 {
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem 0;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    color: var(--primary-color);
  }
  .cta-btn {
    display: inline-block;
    margin-top: 0.5rem;
    padding: 0.6rem 1rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    text-decoration: none;
    border-radius: 8px;
    background: var(--primary-color);
    color: white;
    transition: transform 0.06s ease, opacity 0.1s ease;
  }
  .cta-btn:hover { transform: translateY(-1px); }
  .cta-btn.ghost {
    background: transparent;
    color: var(--primary-color);
    box-shadow: 0 0 0 1px var(--primary-color) inset;
  }
  .cta-btn.ghost:hover { opacity: 0.9; }

  .sidebar {
    display: grid;
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .excerpt { display: grid; gap: 0.75rem; }
  .quote {
    font-style: italic;
    color: #555;
    padding: 0.85rem 1rem;
    border-left: 4px solid var(--primary-color);
    background-color: #f2f3f5;
    border-radius: 6px;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .card {
    padding: 1rem;
    background: #f9f9f9;
    border-radius: 8px;
    box-shadow: 0 0 0 1px rgba(0,0,0,0.04) inset;
  }
  .card h3 {
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem 0;
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    color: var(--primary-color);
  }
  .card p { margin: 0; line-height: 1.6; }

  .text-link {
    display: inline-block;
    margin-top: 0.5rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--secondary-color);
    text-decoration: none;
  }
  .text-link:hover { color: var(--accent-color); }

  .checklist {
    margin: 0.25rem 0 0 1rem;
    padding: 0;
    list-style: disc;
  }
  .checklist li { margin: 0.25rem 0; }

  .activity-lead { margin: 0 0 0.5rem 0; }
  .activity-steps {
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem 1.25rem;
    padding: 0;
  }
  .activity-steps li { margin: 0.25rem 0; }
  .activity-close { margin: 0.5rem 0 0 0; }

/* Muted accent variations pulled from your gradient */
.card.orange {
  background-color: #fff4e6; /* pale orange */
}
.card.blue {
  background-color: #e6f0ff; /* pale blue */
}
.card.purple {
  background-color: #f8f0ff; /* pale purple */
}

.details, .sidebar { flex: 1; min-width: 0; } /* prevents flex overflow */

.book-graphic {
  display: block;
  width: 100%;
  max-width: 320px;
  height: auto;
  margin: 0 auto 1.25rem auto;
  border-radius: 8px;
  box-shadow: 0 6px 16px rgba(0,0,0,0.08);
}

@media (min-width: 768px) {
  .book-graphic {
    margin: 0 0 1rem 0; /* aligns with heading on desktop */
  }
}
</style>
